      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Inspect available columns\n",
        "\n",
        "This helps confirm what metadata is already present."
      ],
      "id": "b1ba5fe7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "#| code-overflow: wrap\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Chunk columns:\")\n",
        "print(df_chunks.columns.tolist())\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nSection columns:\")\n",
        "print(df_sections.columns.tolist())"
      ],
      "id": "fcfc566e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Create minimal filing-level metadata\n",
        "\n",
        "If the current extraction pipeline only preserved `file_name` and `file_path`, we can still build a useful retrieval table with those.\n",
        "\n",
        "If later you add richer metadata such as `company_name`, `cik`, `filing_date`, `accession_number`, or `sic`, this merge step can be extended.\n",
        "\n",
        "For now, we will derive a minimal metadata table from `df_sections`."
      ],
      "id": "d8d8364f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "#| code-overflow: wrap\n",
        "\n",
        "metadata_cols = [col for col in [\n",
        "    \"file_name\",\n",
        "    \"file_path\",\n",
        "    \"company_name\",\n",
        "    \"cik\",\n",
        "    \"filing_date\",\n",
        "    \"accession_number\",\n",
        "    \"sic\",\n",
        "    \"sector\"\n",
        "] if col in df_sections.columns]\n",
        "\n",
        "df_metadata = df_sections[metadata_cols].drop_duplicates().copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(df_metadata.shape)\n",
        "df_metadata.head().style.hide(axis=\"index\")"
      ],
      "id": "0b3cbada",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "If only `file_name` and `file_path` exist, that is fine.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Merge metadata into chunk corpus"
      ],
      "id": "0fb47838"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "#| code-overflow: wrap\n",
        "\n",
        "merge_keys = [col for col in [\"file_name\", \"file_path\"] if col in df_chunks.columns and col in df_metadata.columns]\n",
        "\n",
        "df_retrieval = df_chunks.merge(\n",
        "    df_metadata,\n",
        "    on=merge_keys,\n",
        "    how=\"left\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(df_retrieval.shape)\n",
        "df_retrieval.head().style.hide(axis=\"index\")"
      ],
      "id": "86ad059e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Add retrieval-friendly metadata fields\n",
        "\n",
        "Now we create a few standardized fields that will be useful later for vector search and RAG filtering."
      ],
      "id": "770289f0"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "#| code-overflow: wrap\n",
        "df_retrieval[\"document_type\"] = \"10-K\"\n",
        "df_retrieval[\"filing_year\"] = 2024\n",
        "df_retrieval[\"source_type\"] = \"sec_html_extracted\"\n",
        "df_retrieval[\"retrieval_unit\"] = \"sentence_window_chunk\""
      ],
      "id": "94fbb441",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "If `section_name` exists, normalize it:"
      ],
      "id": "4badf192"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "SECTION_LABELS = {\n",
        "    \"item_1\": \"Item 1 - Business\",\n",
        "    \"item_1a\": \"Item 1A - Risk Factors\",\n",
        "    \"item_7\": \"Item 7 - MD&A\"\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "df_retrieval[\"section_label\"] = df_retrieval[\"section_name\"].map(SECTION_LABELS).fillna(df_retrieval[\"section_name\"])"
      ],
      "id": "918c60fb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Clean and standardize chunk text\n",
        "\n",
        "We want the final retrieval text to be consistently formatted."
      ],
      "id": "eef6f31f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "#| code-overflow: wrap\n",
        "\n",
        "def clean_chunk_text(text: str) -> str:\n",
        "    text = str(text)\n",
        "    text = text.replace(\"\\xa0\", \" \")\n",
        "    text = re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text)\n",
        "    return text.strip()"
      ],
      "id": "a6e83b8c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| eval: true\n",
        "#| code-overflow: wrap\n",
        "\n",
        "df_retrieval[\"chunk_text\"] = df_retrieval[\"chunk_text\"].apply(clean_chunk_text)"
      ],
      "id": "bb744403",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
